<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-689-444  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 689 444  OV: 07 689 370.andO; </DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Sept 25 1989 v11 n39 p64(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Microsoft Project 4.0. (Software Review) (1 of 6project-management software evaluations in 'Mission: madepossible.') (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Heck, Michael.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Microsoft Corp's $495 Microsoft Project 4.0 has many powerfulfeatures, including calendars and resource leveling, but hasfallen behind its competition in some respects.andP;  The programautomatically prorates costs when the user enters the percentagecompleted, a less flexible approach than letting users enteractual figures.andP;  Resource leveling is automatic, but the programhas no resource-limited leveling feature.andP;  Project 4.0 offers onlysatisfactory schedule calculation time and reporting features.andO;The program is very easy to learn, offering few cryptic optionsettings.andP;  It lacks an outliner or other way to start tasks with ageneral view.andP;  Ease of use is rated good, with reports simple toproduce and edit.andP;  It warns the user of logic errors but not ofinvalid resource types.andP;  Documentation is very good, but usersupport is only satisfactory.andP;  Value is rated good.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (products).andO;Ticker:    MSFT.andO;Product:   Microsoft Project 4.0 (Project management software).andO;Topic:     Project ManagementSoftware PackagesEvaluation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>